OL,4,CRail services to come under unified
OL,5,Cstate control
OL,6, The government has announced the
OL,7, biggest shake-up in the UK's railways
OL,8, since privatisation in the mid-1990s.
OL,10,FThe reform plan will see the creation
OL,11,Fof a new state-owned body, Great
OL,12,FBritish Railways (GBR), which will own
OL,13,Fand manage rail infrastructure.
OL,15,FBut there will still be a role for the
OL,16,Fprivate sector, with private operators
OL,17,Fcontracted to run most trains.
OL,19,FAnd next month, flexible season tickets
OL,20,Fwill be available for some people who
OL,21,Fcommute two or three times a week.
